<TITLE> PM seeks more Korean investment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 4 (bdnews24.com)--Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has urged the South Korean entrepreneurs for greater investment in Bangladesh, a government spokesman said. Hasina also called for the Koreans to import more from Bangladesh when the South Korean ambassador Taiyoung Cho called on her, Abul Kalam Azad, the prime minister's press secretary, said at a press briefing on Tuesday after the meeting. The prime minister and the ambassador discussed her forthcoming visit to Korea scheduled for the middle of this month. Azad said they had discussed various regional and international matters alongside issues related to expansion of trade. The prime minister said Bangladesh highly values its ties with Asian economic powerhouse. Hasina told Cho the Korean language would be researched at the International Mother Language Institute in Dhaka. The ambassador hoped the bilateral relation would be strengthened by the expansion of trade. bd
